TY  - JOUR
T1  - Developing a Comprehensive Model of Motivation and Performance: A Methodological Comment
AU  - Goronzy, Friedhelm
Y1  - 1968/09/01
PY  - 1968
DA  - 1968/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/254758
DO  - 10.5465/254758
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 341
EP  - 342
VL  - 11
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article presents a comment on ?Developing a Comprehensive Model of Motivation and Performance,? by Kae H. Chung which appeared in the March 1968 issue of ?The Academy of Management Journal.? The author takes issue with Dr. Chung's methodology, as the author finds that Chung limited himself to univariate statistics for analysis. The article breaks down the methodology that Chung used and offers suggestions as to what worked and what did not. The author applauds Chung for building a multivariate model of motivation and performance and suggests a possible formulation for analysis of Performance, Ability, and Needs.
AB  - The article presents a comment on ?Developing a Comprehensive Model of Motivation and Performance,? by Kae H. Chung which appeared in the March 1968 issue of ?The Academy of Management Journal.? The author takes issue with Dr. Chung's methodology, as the author finds that Chung limited himself to univariate statistics for analysis. The article breaks down the methodology that Chung used and offers suggestions as to what worked and what did not. The author applauds Chung for building a multivariate model of motivation and performance and suggests a possible formulation for analysis of Performance, Ability, and Needs.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/254758
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/254758
Y2  - 2026/04/24
