TY  - JOUR
T1  - Management Discipline in a School of Administration: A Reappraisal in the Public Service Perspective
AU  - Yoon, B. Man
Y1  - 1968/09/01
PY  - 1968
DA  - 1968/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/254753
DO  - 10.5465/254753
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 279
EP  - 289
VL  - 11
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The circumferences of an academic discipline as artificial constructions must be treated as tentative and provisional. A survey of relevant literature suggests that management in the public service may well be a fruitful area in which the management discipline can make significant contributions. It may well be the dimension that the discipline must explore in order to advance to a higher-order theoretical construction of General Administration. In a school of administration of tomorrow the management discipline as a viable concept may have to embrace management of both business and public enterprises.
AB  - The circumferences of an academic discipline as artificial constructions must be treated as tentative and provisional. A survey of relevant literature suggests that management in the public service may well be a fruitful area in which the management discipline can make significant contributions. It may well be the dimension that the discipline must explore in order to advance to a higher-order theoretical construction of General Administration. In a school of administration of tomorrow the management discipline as a viable concept may have to embrace management of both business and public enterprises.
