PY  - 1968
DA  - 1968/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/254760
DO  - 10.5465/254760
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 346
EP  - 347
VL  - 11
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article presents a response to an earlier article titled ?The Management Internship,? by George J. Gore, which appeared in a previous issue of ?Academy of Management Journal.? The author of this response notes the lack of data to prove Gore's point that the cooperative educational experience is more valuable than a traditional BBA. The author suggests that any university considering a cooperative program evaluate samples of both cooperatively educated and noncooperatively educated students on the basis of knowledge, motivations, etc. and look at longitudinal studies of employment records of both students to gauge employee success.
AB  - The article presents a response to an earlier article titled ?The Management Internship,? by George J. Gore, which appeared in a previous issue of ?Academy of Management Journal.? The author of this response notes the lack of data to prove Gore's point that the cooperative educational experience is more valuable than a traditional BBA. The author suggests that any university considering a cooperative program evaluate samples of both cooperatively educated and noncooperatively educated students on the basis of knowledge, motivations, etc. and look at longitudinal studies of employment records of both students to gauge employee success.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/254760
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/254760
Y2  - 2026/04/24
